cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.IT, cs.DM, cs.CG. 

The paper deals with a problem in data structures (finding three binary words that satisfy a certain condition), which suggests that it belongs to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) category. The use of integer sorting algorithms and hash tables also suggests that it could belong to the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.IT (Information Theory) categories. The paper also discusses reductions to other problems, which is a common theme in the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) category. Finally, the use of linear hash functions and the mention of triangle enumeration suggest that it could also belong to the cs.CG (Computational Geometry) category.
